vintage.name: Vintage Leather Suitcase (c1949) Tan Good condition
vintage.description: Vintage leather suitcase from AR Arflite. Made from top grain cow hide. Purchased May 1, 1949 by my father -- Arnold Carmon Mangle (ACM), who apparently had it monogrammed on the outside near the handle. Snazzy!Brass hardware throughout. Both exterior latches work. They have keyholes, but they're not locked, and I don't have the key. Tan leather exterior is well worn, and the leather has numerous cracks along the top edges. The handle is a hand form-fitting molded plastic. Very comfortable. Probably made from Catalin, and likely considered a high-tech feature for that era.Interior is lined with beige canvas throughout. Very clean. Spaces are smartly divided with latching panel, tension-locked pockets, and a zippered cover overlaying divided sub-compartments. Under the latching panel is a suit/dress compartment with 2 removable custom-designed hangers. The plastic hangars, again probably Catalin, mount on a brass peg within the suitcase to keep them in place during travel. But then standard-sized brass hooks swivel into place once you reach the closet at your destination.Obviously a lot of thought went into this design. I imagine it was a top-of-the-line product at the time. If you're one to eschew rolling luggage in favor of genuine leather from a bygone era, this is the suitcase for you! Give your vintage wardrobe the retro accessory it deserves!

famous.name: SISTRUM MUSICAL INSTRUMENT
famous.description: FOR SALE: SISTRUM MUSICAL INSTRUMENT, $60.  Replica of an ancient Sistrum (rattle).  These were used as musical percussion instruments for various rites and ceremonies.  The Sistrum first appeared in the Old Kingdom and became connected to the goddesses Isis and Hathor.  Unfortunately very few exist.  Most of the surviving ones come from the Greco-Roman era.  It’s closest modern equivalent is the tambourine and is used the same way.   The Sistrum has a long handle, a frame with crossbars and small disks that rattle when shaken.  They were made of wood, stone or metal.  The word Sistrum means that which is being shaken.  The Egyptians believed that the Sistrum had magical properties. It is connected with the powers of the Goddess and symbolizes joy, fertility and eroticism.  It was believed that the Sistrum could avert the flooding of the Nile.  One of the most famous depictions of the Sistrum is in the Hathor Temple in Dendera.  You will also see depictions of the Goddess Isis with a symbol of inundation in one hand and a Sistrum in the other. All vintage, antique and used items are sold “as found” and are priced accordingly.

famous.name: Roland Jazz Chorus JC 22 Guitar Amplifier
famous.description: Like new solid state amp w/ classic Boss chorus built in.“ The JC-22 Jazz Chorus delivers Roland’s classic JC clean tone and famous Dimensional Space Chorus effect in a compact amp that’s perfect for playing at home. Offering the essential features of the popular JC-40 in an even more scaled-down size, this versatile stereo amp is also great for intimate performances and recording. A high-quality reverb complements the onboard chorus, and there’s also a stereo input on the front panel for plugging in modelers, multi-effects, and stereo stomps. Built to the same standards of sound and durability that the long-running amp series is noted for, the JC-22 makes legendary JC tone more accessible than ever.”Want.
